data: Great Barrier Reef, Australia
The world's largest coral reef system, known for its vibrant marine life and stunning underwater landscapes.
Grand Canyon, USA
A natural wonder carved by the Colorado River, offering breathtaking views and extensive hiking trails.
Machu Picchu, Peru
An ancient Incan city set high in the Andes Mountains, renowned for its archaeological significance and panoramic vistas.
Santorini, Greece
A picturesque island famous for its white-washed buildings, stunning sunsets, and clear blue waters.
Banff National Park, Canada
Canada's oldest national park, known for its stunning mountain scenery, crystal-clear lakes, and diverse wildlife.
Taj Mahal, India
A magnificent white marble mausoleum, celebrated as a symbol of love and one of the New Seven Wonders of the World.
Amalfi Coast, Italy
A UNESCO World Heritage site, known for its dramatic cliffs, charming coastal towns, and stunning Mediterranean views.
Kyoto, Japan
A city rich in history and culture, famous for its classical Buddhist temples, beautiful gardens, and traditional wooden houses.
Victoria Falls, Zambia/Zimbabwe
One of the world's largest and most famous waterfalls, known for its impressive height and powerful flow.
Gal√°pagos Islands, Ecuador
An archipelago famed for its unique and diverse wildlife, which inspired Charles Darwin's theory of evolution.
Patagonia, Argentina/Chile
A region known for its rugged landscapes, majestic glaciers, and stunning national parks like Torres del Paine.
Serengeti National Park, Tanzania
Renowned for its annual migration of over 1.5 million wildebeest and numerous other wildlife species.
Petra, Jordan
An ancient city carved into rose-red rock, known for its archaeological and historical significance as well as its breathtaking architecture.
Antelope Canyon, USA
A slot canyon in Arizona known for its wave-like structure and the light beams that shine down into the openings of the canyon.
Iceland
A country known for its dramatic landscapes with volcanoes, geysers, hot springs, and lava fields.
